$interpreted: Eidatyr: Aha, here we are! The seas are as sweet and lovely as I could'a hoped.
Sophie: It's the ocean... I had no idea we were so close to the sea.
Eidatyr: The clan's territory is surrounded by mountains. This is the only corner from which you can go out to sea.
Eidatyr: Hidden away as they are, the clan forbids its people from venturing out to sea. Very few even know about this place.
Hutchinson: Okay then, Captain Eidatyr, so how did you know about it?
Eidatyr: Uh... I happened across it when I was little. More or less.
Ru-yi: Ahh, really? What good fortune~
Eidatyr: ...I stumbled in here and broke the clan's prohibition. They stripped me of my runes and sent me into exile.
Ru-yi: Ohhh, I-I'm sorry, I didn't know...
Eidatyr: Bwahaha, don't worry about it!
Eidatyr: ...The sea was my destiny. Unlike fortune, there's nothing good or bad about destiny.
Eidatyr: Just like how you lot came across Rune, am I right?
Sophie: Eidatyr...
Sophie: Yeah! You're right!
Eidatyr: Okay! So, if we're gonna get our paws on that destiny of yours that you've been missing so much, we'll need to spring an ambush from right here!
Eidatyr: Theodore and his supporters are certain to mobilize here.
Sophie: I'm not missing him that much...
Hanbei: Are you sure about that? What if they decide to set sail from Westport...
Eidatyr: Impossible. The road to Westport is patrolled by clan soldiers.
Hanbei: Even so, it's been a few days already. They'd have left already...
Eidatyr: —Even more impossible.
Eidatyr: I have a little habit... Even if I can't actually see it from where I am, I'm always monitoring the seas and their situation.
Eidatyr: And unless I've miscalculated, there's been no way to set sail for several days now.
Hanbei: But what if they insisted anyway—
Eidatyr: Insisted? Never underestimate the sea. If I can't make it out on those waters, then there's not a chance anyone else could.
Eidatyr: But today... Today's a perfect day for setting sail. Just you wait, they're sure to show up.
Ru-yi: But we've waited so long already. Is anyone really gonna come along now—
Eidatyr: Shhh, they're coming! Quick, hide yourselves!
Rune: Master says, wait here.
Valdrir: You don't understand, I have to go back! We all have to go back!!
Valdrir: The day of Lysfete has passed... And weren't we just attacked by monsters?
Rune: I beat monsters. Don't afraid.
Valdrir: That's not the point! If the monsters are appearing, that means the Lysfete has failed, and Vendacti's curse remains.
Valdrir: We're the only ones left who can save the Saga clan and the north!
Rune: ...I, don't understand?
Valdrir: What... What don't you understand... That's the fate we were born for...!
Eidatyr: Don't blame him. Even a clan member like me doesn't understand why it's necessary to drop a baby into a volcano. Just what kind of sacred mission is that, anyway?
Rune: So...phie? Everyone...?!
Valdrir: ...Eidatyr...!
Eidatyr: Hey you two, long time no see.
Sophie: You're both okay! This is wonderful~ I was so worried about you.
Sophie: We've come to help you, Rune. If we all put our heads together, we're sure to find a way to beat Theodore. Just let her go first, and then...
Rune: ...No.
Eidatyr: ......
Rune: Master ordered, Rune, guard Valdrir.
Hanbei: You nincompoop, what's the matter with you? Why do you sound all peculiar like that?
Rune: I, not letting you, in Master's way.
Sophie: Theodore is not your master! You're free, Rune, free!
Rune: ...Free... is too hard... for Rune.
Sophie: Rune...!
Rune: Don't want... Valdrir dies. Theodore says, can do it. So, Theodore, is Master.
Eidatyr: Save your breath. It's time to let our fists do the talking!
Rune: Rune, can't lose. Must protect...
Hutchinson: Ahahaha... I almost forgot how quickly Rune recovers...
Eidatyr: Tch, when's this gonna stop.
Ru-yi: Oh no! We can't beat Rune! He's breaking the rules! I don't wanna play anymoooore!
Sophie: Oh, for crying out loud! Stop that, Rune! Look, you've made Ru-yi cry! Apologize, right this instant!
Rune: ...But... You, left Rune, first. All alone. Rune all by himself.
Rune: ...Sophie, is a liar.
Sophie: Huh? But I never stopped writing to you?
Rune: ...Sophie, wrote me?
Sophie: I'm the one who should be asking you why you never replied. I sent you so many!
Rune: Rune... never got... Did Master...?
Eidatyr: —Now!
Eidatyr: Quit dozing and tie him up! Or do you wanna keep on fighting him?!
Rune: I... Sophie...
Sophie: It's okay, Rune. I know it's not your fault...
Eidatyr: Guh, what a load of bother...
Valdrir: ...Is it... Is it really you, Eidatyr?
Eidatyr: ...You're still shivering. We can talk later.
Valdrir: Why did you come back... You said you'd forsaken the north for good...
Eidatyr: Some idiot of a Clan Mother you are, getting fooled so easily! Were your brains frosted over when you agreed to Theodore's terms or what!
Valdrir: I... I was foolish, but I tried my best...
Valdrir: I waited... I waited so long for you to come back to Westport...
Eidatyr: ...Uh, wait. You don't mean...
Valdrir: I thought you'd really abandoned the north... Abandoned me... I really thought... I...
Eidatyr: Goddammit, I knew this would happen...
Valdrir: *sob*... I... *sob*...
Eidatyr: Hey, you can cry or you can talk, but not at the same time, you idiot!
Valdrir: I... I.. Bwuhuhu...
Eidatyr: Okay okay, I'm sorry for yelling! Stop crying!
Theodore: I thought you were trustworthy enough to keep your promises, Eidatyr.
